        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 4:12PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 411 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms over
Irby and Lake Stamford, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stamford, Throckmorton, Lake Stamford Marina, Irby, Paint Creek, and
The Intersection Of Us-380 And Highway 222.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
